{{Infobox language |name=Tayart |nativename=Tamajeq |states=[[Niger]] |region=[[Sahara]] |speakers=250,000 |date=1998 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Berber languages|Berber]] |fam3=[[Tuareg languages|Tuareg]] |fam4=Southern |iso3=thz |glotto=taya1257 |glottorefname=Tayart Tamajeq |dia1=Air (Tayiṛt) |dia2=Tanassfarwat (Tamagarast) }} '''Air Tamajeq''' (''Tayiṛt'') is a variety of [[Tamasheq language|Tamasheq]], one of the [[Tuareg languages]]. It is spoken by the [[Tuareg people]] inhabiting the [[Aïr Mountains]], in the [[Agadez Region]] of [[Niger]].
''[[Ethnologue]]'' lists two dialects: ''Air (Tayert)'' and ''Tanassfarwat (Tamagarast/Tamesgrest)''. Blench (2006) considers these two varieties to be distinct languages. He lists ''Ingal'' and ''Gofat'' as dialects of Air/Tayirt and Azerori as a dialect of Tamesgrest.
