'''Army Golf Club'''<ref>{{cite web|title=Cut fare by 15pc for 1st 2km: PM|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/cut-fare-by-15pc-for-1st-2km-pm-21126|website=thedailystar.net|accessdate=28 September 2016|date=22 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.banglatribune.com/business/news/186119/%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%97%E0%A6%B2%E0%A6%AB-%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B2%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B2%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B2-%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A5%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%8B|title=আর্মি গলফ ক্লাবে সোলার প্যানেল স্থাপন করলো ম্যাক্স গ্রুপ {{!}} banglatribune.com|work=Bangla Tribune|access-date=2018-05-29|language=bn}}</ref> is a golf club in [[Dhaka Cantonment]], [[Bangladesh]] operated by [[Bangladesh Army]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Lightning deaths prevention to get priority in US, Bangladesh civil-military exercise|url=http://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2016/09/26/lightning-deaths-prevention-to-get-priority-in-us-bangladesh-civil-military-exercise|website=bdnews24.com|accessdate=28 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=US-Bangladesh army joint workshop on disaster response begins|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/country/us-bangladesh-army-joint-workshop-disaster-response-begins-135028|website=thedailystar.net|accessdate=28 September 2016|date=30 August 2015}}</ref> The present president of the club Major General SM Motiur Rahman, afwc,psc <ref>{{cite web|title=President - Army Golf Club|url=http://agc.com.bd/WS/President|website=agc.com.bd|accessdate=28 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bangladeshi NDC delegation meets Secretary|url=http://www.defence.lk/new.asp?fname=Bangladeshi_NDC_delegation_meets_Secretary_20160816_02|website=www.defence.lk|accessdate=28 September 2016}}</ref>
==History== [[File:Golf Garden.jpg|thumb]]
Army Golf Club was founded on 28 May 2001. It was opened by the first President of the Club and then Chief of Army Staff Lt General [[M Harun-Ar-Rashid]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Home - Army Golf Club|url=http://agc.com.bd/WS/|website=agc.com.bd|accessdate=28 September 2016}}</ref> [[Bangladesh Golf Academy]], first golf academy of Bangladesh was opened on 9 June 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Golf academy opens amid hush-hush|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/sports/golf/golf-academy-opens-amid-hush-hush-94642|website=thedailystar.net|accessdate=28 September 2016|date=9 June 2015}}</ref> The club is affiliated with Kurmitola Golf Club. It has a 9-hole course and over 40 acre in size.<ref>{{cite web|title=THE GOLF STORY|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/the-golf-story-25606|website=thedailystar.net|accessdate=28 September 2016|date=26 May 2014}}</ref> Golf garden restaurant is located in the club.<ref>{{cite web|title=Home Page|url=http://www.golfgardenbd.com/|website=www.golfgardenbd.com|accessdate=28 September 2016}}</ref>
