'''Gayil''' (also called '''Gayl''', '''Gayi''', '''Galila''', '''Gelila''', '''Northern Ari''') is an [[Omotic languages|Omotic]] language of [[Ethiopia]]. According to the 2007 census, 55,700 people speak Gayil as a [[mother tongue]].

